    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose to observe transitional disk, T56, with the ALMA band7 continuum, CO (J=3–2), and HCO+ (J=4–3) line observation. The purpose of this program is to detect a new transitional disk with asymmetric structure around low-mass pre-main sequence star by means of high spatial resolution observation in ∼ 0.12” scale in order to examine how the dust grains are distributed in low mass disk and grow to planetesimals. With a previously conducted aperture polarimetric observation at seeing limit in JHK bands, we found that T56 had significantly highly polarized emission (3.78 ± 0.24 %) and low extinction (Av = 0.60). Based upon the results of IRSF/SIRPOL and Subaru observation so far, the disk with high polarization degree around low-mass star is extremely unique and it might be caused by the highly asymmetric dust disk structure such as AB Aur and HD 142527 (Hashimoto et al. 2011; Fukagawa et al. 2006). This observation can answer what triggers the asymmetric structure formation and how it proceeds.</prp:abstract>
